cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a geometric combinatorial optimization problem and proposes an algorithm that uses Delaunay triangulations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the size of fundamental combinatorial structures called epsilon-nets and proposes an algorithm to compute them efficiently. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems and proposes a constructive proof. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper discusses approximation algorithms and their performance. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes an algorithm that can be implemented in near-linear time.
